other_tests.findings: Cerebrospinal fluid examination showed no increase in leukocytes and normal levels of protein, glucose, and acetylcholinesterase; cytologic analysis showed no malignant tumor cells.
Pathological examination revealed a normal anterior pituitary gland with no evidence of granulomas or inflammation.
Specimens contained fragments of normal kidney; the perirenal fat had an infiltrate of bland-appearing histiocytic cells, mixed with lymphocytes. No evidence of granulomas or vasculitis was found.
